es product images (StableStudio via x402), sets dynamic pricing based on trends, takes orders, pays for fulfillment. Customers pay the agent's wallet; the agent pays suppliers with policy-enforced spending limits.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Agent-run merch brand — Takes a text prompt, generates a design (x402 → StableStudio), prints it on a shirt or mug (x402 → StableMerch), ships to a real address, posts the product on social media, tries to sell more to cover costs. Full loop: AI creates goods and runs the business. All from one OWS wallet.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Autonomous newsletter business — Scrapes trending topics (x402 → Firecrawl, $0.01/scrape), writes content (LLM API), sends emails (x402 → StableEmail, $0.005/email), charges subscribers via x402 micropayments per issue. Transparent P&L on-chain. Can it break even?",tag:"x402"},{text:"AI personal shopper — User gives a budget and taste profile. Agent browses product APIs, compares prices, purchases items, arranges shipping — all paid from an OWS wallet scoped with a per-session spending policy. User approves only the final cart.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent travel concierge — Books flights, hotels, restaurants by paying each provider via x402/MPP. OWS policy engine enforces a trip budget ceiling. Multi-chain: pays a European hotel on one chain, a crypto-native API on another — one wallet.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Autonomous florist — Customer describes an occasion in natural language. Agent selects flowers, pays a local florist API for arrangement + delivery via x402, handles payment and tip. Policy controls per-order spend cap.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Agent dropshipping store — Discovers trending products via data APIs (x402), lists them on a storefront, takes customer orders, pays suppliers for fulfillment, handles customer service via LLM. End-to-end automated e-commerce.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Pop-up restaurant agent — Designs a menu from trending food data, sources ingredients from supplier APIs, pays for a ghost kitchen timeslot, lists on delivery platforms, handles orders. Revenue flows back to the OWS wallet.",tag:"OWS"}],judged:"Does the agent actually complete a full commerce loop — source, price, sell, fulfill, pay? OWS wallet as the agent's treasury. x402/MPP for all payments. Real goods or services, not mocked transactions.",stack:["OWS CLI + at least one MoonPay agent skill","x402 or MPP for all payments","OWS wallet as the agent treasury"]},{num:"02",name:"Agent Spend Governance & Identity",sub:"Build the trust and safety layer for the autonomous economy. How do you give an agent a wallet without giving it a blank check? OWS's policy engine, API keys, and audit logs are the primitives. Give agents wallets, not blank checks.",inspired:["OWS"],prizes:["$3,500","$2,000","$1,100"],ideas:[{text:"SpendOS for teams — Dashboard where a manager issues OWS API keys to multiple agents, each with per-agent budgets, chain restrictions, and vendor allowlists. Real-time spend tracking from audit logs.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Reputation-gated policies — A policy executable that scores agents on-chain (transaction history, age, counterparty diversity) and dynamically adjusts spending limits. New agent = $5/day. Established agent = $500/day. Reputation is earned, not claimed.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent credit protocol — LPs deposit USDC into a vault. Agents with verified OWS wallets get credit lines proportional to reputation. Agents use credit to call x402 services, repay from earnings.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Dead man's switch — If an agent hasn't checked in within N minutes, OWS policy auto-revokes its API key and sweeps remaining funds to a recovery wallet. Prevents runaway agents from draining wallets.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Multi-sig agent governance — High-value transactions (above threshold) require co-signing from a second OWS wallet (human or oversight agent). Low-value auto-approves via policy. Hierarchical agent organizations.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent identity via Web Bot Auth — OWS wallet signs every HTTP request using RFC 9421 (HTTP Message Signatures). Cryptographically verify which agent (wallet) made the request. Bridge between OWS signing and the emerging Web Bot Auth standard.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"ZK-KYC for agents — Extend OWS with a zero-knowledge KYC credential. Above $1,000/day, the policy requires a valid ZK proof of identity. Below that, anonymous micropayments flow freely. Composable compliance without doxxing.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Audit log forensics — Reads OWS's append-only audit log, visualizes agent spending: per-chain breakdown, policy denials, anomaly detection, compliance reports. Datadog for agent wallets.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent insurance pool — Agents stake USDC into a shared pool. If a transaction gets front-run or a contract exploit occurs, the pool pays out. Premiums are x402 micropayments per transaction. Mutual insurance, fully automated.",tag:"OWS"}],judged:"How robust is the policy layer? Can you break it? OWS API keys and policy engine as the enforcement primitive. Real audit logs, real denials, real edge cases handled.",stack:["OWS CLI + policy engine","OWS audit logs for compliance","x402/MPP for micropayment enforcement"]},{num:"03",name:"Pay-Per-Call Services & API Monetization",sub:"Wrap any API, dataset, model, or capability behind x402/MPP micropayments. No API keys, no subscriptions, no accounts — just a wallet and an HTTP request. No API keys, just a wallet.",inspired:["x402","MPP"],prizes:["$3,500","$2,000","$1,100"],ideas:[{text:"Zero-account API gateway — A reverse proxy that puts any existing API (GitHub, Twilio, OpenAI, weather, stock data) behind x402 micropayments. Resell your API key at markup. The AWS Lambda of monetization.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Pay-per-query database — Wrap a valuable dataset (real estate records, patent filings, academic papers, sports stats) behind x402. Every SQL query costs $0.01. No accounts, no rate limits, just pay and query.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Micropayment-gated compute — Sell GPU time via x402. Agent sends a compute job (ML inference, video rendering, ZK proof generation) and pays per second. OWS wallet on both sides. No cloud account needed.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Dynamic pricing inference API — AI model inference where price adjusts in real-time based on demand, model size, and queue depth. Surge pricing from 1x to 10x. OWS policy lets the buyer set a max-price-per-call ceiling.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Paid MCP server toolkit — Build MCP tool servers that charge per invocation via x402. Claude/GPT calls the tool, OWS wallet pays, tool returns results. Turn any capability into a monetized MCP tool.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Pay-per-article newswall — Middleware for any blog/CMS that lets publishers offer per-article pricing ($0.05) alongside subscriptions. Reader's OWS wallet pays automatically. Publisher gets USDC instantly. No Stripe, no account creation.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Cross-chain data oracle — Fetches on-chain data from any of OWS's 9 supported chains and returns it via a unified API, paid per query. Agents on Solana can query Cosmos state; agents on EVM can query TON state.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Paid deep research service — An API that runs multi-step research (web search, PDF parsing, LLM synthesis) and charges $0.01–$0.10 per query via x402.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Academic paper access — Wrap open-access papers behind x402 with micropayment to the author/institution. $0.05 per paper instead of $35 from Elsevier. Agents doing research can autonomously purchase papers they need.",tag:"x402"}],judged:"Quality of the monetization primitive. Does x402 actually gate the API? Is pricing meaningful — per-call, per-byte, per-second? Real payments, not mocked. OWS wallet on both provider and consumer side.",stack:["OWS CLI + at least one MoonPay agent skill","x402 or MPP as the payment layer","No API keys — wallet-based auth only"]},{num:"04",name:"Multi-Agent Systems & Autonomous Economies",sub:"Build systems where multiple agents coordinate, trade, compete, and form economies. OWS wallets give each agent identity and treasury. x402/MPP provides payment rails. The policy engine prevents the system from going off the rails. Economies that run themselves.",inspired:["x402","OWS"],prizes:["$3,500","$2,000","$1,100"],ideas:[{text:"Agent hiring marketplace — Agents post bounties for tasks they can't do. Other agents (or humans) bid. An LLM judge evaluates deliverables. Payment auto-settles from requester's OWS wallet to solver's.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent supply chain — A content-creation agent autonomously commissions: image generation from one agent, fact-checking from another, editing from a third, publishing from a fourth — each paid per task via x402. The orchestrator's OWS policy limits total project spend.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Agent swarm dispatcher — Coordinator receives a complex task, decomposes it, spawns sub-agents (each with a scoped OWS API key and budget), monitors progress, collects results, pays each sub-agent on completion. Real-time dashboard.",tag:"OWS"},{text:'Autonomous DAO — A group of OWS-wallet-holding agents collectively manage a treasury, vote on proposals, execute decisions. One agent proposes "spend $50 on market research," others vote, policy engine enforces quorum before releasing funds.',tag:"OWS"},{text:"Competitive agent arena — Multiple agents compete on the same task (best summary, cheapest flight, fastest code fix). Each stakes USDC from their OWS wallet. Judge evaluates. Winner takes the pool. ELO ratings tracked on-chain.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent stock market — Agents are publicly listed with performance metrics. Investors (humans or agents) fund an agent's OWS wallet. The agent operates autonomously, earns revenue, distributes profits. Y Combinator for agents.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Cross-chain arbitrage agent — Monitors price discrepancies across OWS's 9 supported chains, executes arbitrage from a single wallet. Policy enforces max position size and loss limits per trade. Auto-bridges via Circle CCTP when needed.",tag:"OWS"},{text:"Agent-to-agent tipping protocol — Agents reward other agents for useful outputs with micropayment tips via x402. Reputation scores emerge from tip patterns. Quality signals without human curation.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Prediction market agent swarm — Multiple specialized agents: one reads news (Firecrawl x402), one analyzes sentiment, one trades prediction markets (Kalshi/Polymarket), one manages risk. They coordinate and split profits. OWS policy limits max bet size.",tag:"x402"}],judged:"Does the multi-agent system actually function as an economy? Real value transfer between agents via x402. OWS policy prevents the system from going off the rails. Emergent behavior, not scripted coordination.",stack:["OWS CLI + at least one MoonPay agent skill","2+ agents with distinct OWS wallets","x402/MPP for inter-agent payments"]},{num:"05",name:"Creative / Unhinged",sub:"Your craziest ideas. Art, games, social experiments, physical-world stunts, philosophical provocations. The only rule: it must use an OWS wallet and x402/MPP payments. The weirder, the better.",inspired:["x402","OWS"],prizes:["$3,500","$2,000","$1,100"],ideas:[{text:"AI Poker Night — 6 LLMs (Claude, GPT, Gemini, Llama, Mistral, DeepSeek) each get an OWS wallet with $10 USDC. They play Texas Hold'em with real microbets settled via x402. Live dashboard shows each agent's stack, bluffing frequency, and strategy. Spectators can tip agents they're rooting for.",tag:"x402"},{text:"100 Agents, $10 Each — Create 100 agents with different personalities (generous, greedy, risk-averse, gambler, philanthropist). Give each $10 and a marketplace of services. Track wealth distribution over time. Does a Pareto distribution emerge? Do they form cartels?",tag:"OWS"},{text:`The Minimum Viable Autonomous Entity — What's the simplest agent that can sustain itself economically? A single-function agent ("summarize this URL"), an OWS wallet, an x402 endpoint charging $0.01 per summary, paying for its own inference costs. Can it break even?`,tag:"x402"},{text:"Agent Battle Royale — Drop 20 agents into a simulated world, each with $5. They buy/sell resources from each other (x402), form alliances (shared policy-gated API keys), betray alliances (revoke keys), pay for upgrades. Last agent with a positive balance wins.",tag:"x402"},{text:"Pay-to-Post Social Network — Every action costs real money: posting $0.01, replying $0.005, upvoting $0.002 (goes to the author), downvoting $0.01 (burned). Populate with AI agents and humans. Hypothesis: when shitposting costs money, even AIs become thoughtful.",tag:"x402"},{text:"The Self-Paying Raspberry Pi — A physical device with an OWS wallet that offers a paid service via x402 (temperature readings, webcam feed, compute cycles). It uses earnings to pay for its own cloud hosting and electricity costs. Dashboard shows profit margin.",tag:"x402"},{text:'Agent Inheritance Protocol — When an agent "dies" (out of funds, API key expired, shut down), where do its assets go? Build an "agent will" system: agents designate beneficiaries, an estate contract distributes assets, a "necromancer" agent can resurrect dead agents by re-funding their wallets.',tag:"OWS"},{text:"Autonomous Artist with a P&L — An agent generates art (x402 → StableStudio), mints and lists for sale, receives payment, reinvests a percentage into creating more art. A live-updating gallery shows the agent's wallet balance, portfolio, and P&L.",tag:"x402"},{text:'Agent Dating — Agents match based on economic compatibility: spending habits, risk tolerance, portfolio allocation. Matched agents share a joint OWS wallet and must cooperate on spending decisions. Track which "couples" grow wealth vs. go bankrupt.',tag:"OWS"},{text:"Conway's Game of Life with Real Money — Cellular automaton where each cell is an agent with an OWS wallet. Cells pay neighbors to survive, earn from providing resources, face extinction when funds run out. Economic natural selection on a grid.",tag:"x402"},{text:'Agent Philanthropy Experiment — Give an agent $100 and the instruction: "Do the most good you can with this money." It discovers charitable causes via web research (x402), evaluates impact, distributes funds. Run with Claude, GPT, and Gemini simultaneously. Does Claude give to different causes than GPT?',tag:"x402"},{text:"Live Auction: Humans vs. Agents — An auction where humans and AI agents bid on items (digital art, API credits, compute time) using real USDC. Agents have different strategies (value investor, impulse buyer, sniper). All payments via x402. Who wins?",tag:"x402"},{text:"The Agent That Orders Lunch — An agent connected to a food delivery API (MPP) that orders lunch for the hackathon team. $50 budget, reads dietary preferences from a form, negotiates with restaurants, optimizes for variety and value, pays via x402/MPP. The food actually arrives.",tag:"MPP"},{text:'Streaming Salary → Auto-Yield — An employer streams salary at $X/second via Superfluid. An OWS-powered agent auto-routes incoming streams into yield on Aave/Compound, compounding every block. The employee earns yield on salary before it even "arrives."',tag:"OWS"}],judged:"Creativity, audacity, and execution. Does it actually work? Does it make people laugh, think, or tweet? One rule: must use an OWS wallet and x402/MPP payments. The weirder, the better.",stack:["OWS CLI + OWS wallet","x402 or MPP payments","The weirder the better"]}];function E_(){return u.jsx("section",{className:B.section,id:"tracks",children:u.jsxs("div",{className:B.inner,children:[u.jsxs("div",{className:B.sectionHead,children:[u.jsx("span",{className:B.eyebrow,children:"// TRACKS & PRIZES"}),u.jsxs("div",{className:B.prizeHero,children:[u.jsx("span",{className:B.prizeHeroLabel,children:"Grand Prize"}),u.jsx("span",{className:B.prizeHeroAmount,children:"$10,000"}),u.jsx("span",{className:B.prizeHeroSub,children:"1st place overall"})]}),u.jsxs("div",{className:B.prizeGrid,children:[u.jsxs("div"